vulnerability.name: USN-7577-2
vulnerability.description: USN-7577-1 fixed a vulnerability in libblockdev. This update provides the corresponding update for Ubuntu 18.04 LTS and Ubuntu 20.04 LTS.  Original advisory details:   It was discovered that libblockdev incorrectly handled mount options when  resizing certain filesystems. A local attacker with an active session on  the console can use this issue to escalate their privileges to root.

statements.status_notes: libblockdev could be made to run programs as an administrator. Available with Ubuntu Pro.
